# Conversation naming — prompt iteration

## Why this notebook exists

`Manillum.Conversations.Conversation.Changes.GenerateName` is the AshOban-triggered
action that produces a short title for each chat conversation once it has a
few messages on it. The original prompt was a single-line system message
("2-8 words, RESPOND WITH ONLY THE NEW CONVERSATION NAME") followed by the raw
conversation history. On a Roman-Empire timeline conversation the model
ignored the instruction and continued the assistant's own bullet-list
reply — landing **301 characters of markdown** in the `title` column
(see conversation `019df9cd-326a-7751-b31e-75446fafa2ef` in the dev DB).

This notebook is the iteration surface for the new prompt
(`Manillum.Conversations.Conversation.NamePrompt`). It runs the new prompt
against a fixture set covering several conversation shapes — the failing
case, a single short exchange, a greeting-only stub, a multi-turn drift
between topics — and reports the model's output, parsed title, and any
length / format violations.

To re-load prompt edits made in `lib/manillum/conversations/conversation/name_prompt.ex`
while the notebook is connected, run `r Manillum.Conversations.Conversation.NamePrompt`.

## Connecting

This notebook expects a Mix standalone runtime against the worktree root.
In Livebook: **Runtime → Mix standalone** → select the repo directory.
Once connected, Manillum modules are available without any extra
`Mix.install` — the prompt module, ReqLLM, and Ash are all on the path.

